What is a Sorting algorithm ?

A Sorting Algorithm is used to arrange a given array or list DS elements according to a particular pattern .

Why do we need a sorting algorithm ?

1) Efficient sorting is important for optimizing the efficiency of other algorithm.
2) Producing more human readable output.
3) It is easier and faster to locate items in a sorted list than unsorted

Types of Sorting Algorithm ?

1) Selection Sort
2) Bubble sort 
3) Insertion Sort
4) Merge Sort
5) Quick Sort
6) Radix Sort
etc.
